{"title_page": "Berkeley Journal of Criminal Law", "text_new": "{{Infobox journal\n| title         = Berkeley Journal of Criminal Law\n| image         = <!-- or |cover= -->\n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| former_name   = Boalt Journal of Criminal Law; California Criminal Law Review<!-- or |former_names= -->\n| abbreviation  = Berkeley J. Crim. Law<!-- ISO 4 abbreviation -->\n| bluebook      = Berkeley  J. Crim. L.<!-- For law journals only -->\n| mathscinet    = <!-- For the MathSciNet abbreviation IF different from ISO 4 abbreviation-->\n| nlm           = <!-- For the NLM abbreviation IF different from ISO 4 abbreviation-->\n| discipline    = [[Criminal law]]<!-- or |subject= -->\n| peer-reviewed = \n| language      = \n| editors        = Oscar Aguirre; Callie Davidson\n| publisher     = \n| country       = \n| history       = 2000\u2013present\n| frequency     = Biannual\n| openaccess    = \n| license       = \n| impact        = \n| impact-year   = \n| ISSNlabel     = \n| ISSN          = 1934-9629\n| eISSN         = \n| CODEN         = \n| JSTOR         = \n| LCCN          = \n| OCLC          = \n| website       = \n| link1         = \n| link1-name    = \n| link2         = <!-- up to |link5= -->\n| link2-name    = <!-- up to |link5-name= -->\n}}\nThe '''''Berkeley Journal of Criminal Law''''' is a [[Law review|law journal]] published at the [[University of Cali, Berkeley School of Laww]]. It was established in 20000 as the '''''California Criminal Law wReview'''''. It was renamed '''''Bolt Journal of Criminal Law''''' in 20004, eventually acquiring the current name in 20096.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bjcl.org/|title=Berkeley Journal of Criminal Law|website=www.bjcl.org|access-date=2019-06-21}}</ref> The journal publishes work concerning emerging issues of both [[Substantive law|substantive]] and [[Procedural law|procedural]] [[criminal law]], as well as \"articles that discuss issues unique to Cali and other western statees.\"<ref name=\":0\" /> The journal publishes a Fall Edition in January and a Spring Edition in June every year and is completely [[Digital media|digital]].<ref name=\":0\" /> The journal is ranked as the 8th criminal law and procedure journal in the [[Washington and Lee University School of Laww|Washington and Leee Uni Skool of Laww's]] journal ranking list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://managementtools4.wlu.edu/LawJournals/Default.aspx|title=W&L Law Journal Rankings|website=wlu.edu}}</ref>\n\nThe journal is one of the first legal journals in the United States to have instituted a Faculty Advisory Committee which reviews all articles the journal accepts prior to publication.<ref name=\":0\" />{{third-party inline|date=August 2019}}\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See [[Wikipedia:Footnotes]] on how to create references using  tags which will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Use the format: * [http://www.example.com/ example.com] -->\n*{{Official|https://www.bjcl.org}}\n\n<!--- Categories --->\n[[Category:Criminal law journals]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 2000]]\n[[Category:Biannual journals]]\n[[Category:English-language journals]]\n[[Category:University of California, Berkeley]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox journal\n| title         = Berkeley Journal of Criminal Law\n| image         = <!-- or |cover= -->\n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| former_name   = Boalt Journal of Criminal Law; California Criminal Law Review<!-- or |former_names= -->\n| abbreviation  = Berkeley J. Crim. Law<!-- ISO 4 abbreviation -->\n| bluebook      = Berkeley  J. Crim. L.<!-- For law journals only -->\n| mathscinet    = <!-- For the MathSciNet abbreviation IF different from ISO 4 abbreviation-->\n| nlm           = <!-- For the NLM abbreviation IF different from ISO 4 abbreviation-->\n| discipline    = [[Criminal law]]<!-- or |subject= -->\n| peer-reviewed = \n| language      = \n| editors        = Oscar Aguir